  "body": "\r\n\r\n# üêû Bug Report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nWhen prysm.sh is launched with the `--config-file` flag, the monitoring port defined in the YAML config is ignored and the default 8080 is used instead.\r\n\r\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\r\n\r\nDon't know.  This is my first time using `--config-file`.\r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\r\n\r\n`./prysm.sh beacon-chain --config-file=$HOME/prysm/onyxbeacon.yaml`\r\n\r\nYAML:\r\n`monitoring-port: 8082`\r\n\r\n## üåç  Your Environment\r\n\r\nLinux Mint 19.3\r\n\r\n**What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)**\r\n\r\n1.0.0.alpha.13\r\n\r\n**Anything else relevant?**\r\n\r\nCould this have anything to do with the fact that MonitoringPortFlag is the only integer flag defined with type Int64Flag instead of IntFlag?  I'm no programmer...\r\nhttps://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/blob/aa52e693ce0a6307bbb68af66b60cc9519810992/beacon-chain/flags/base.go#L35",
